A. GARG-Coated Microtitration Strips:
One stripholder, containing 96 polystyrene microtiter wells with goat anti-rabbit globulin serum
B. Cortisol Antiserum: (Blue)
One vial, 11 mL, containing rabbit anti-cortisol serum in a protein-based (BSA) buffer with a non-mercury preservative.
C. Cortisol Standards:
One vial, 0.5 mL, labeled A, containing 0 μg/dL cortisol and 7 vials, 0.5 mL each, labeled B-H, containing concentrations of approximately 0.5, 1.5, 4.0, 10.0, 20.0, 40.0, and 60.0 μg/dL cortisol in protein-based (BSA) buffer with a non-mercury preservative.
D. Cortisol Controls:
Two vials, 0.5 mL each, Level I and II, containing low and high concentrations of cortisol in protein-based (BSA) buffer with a non-mercury preservative.
E. Cortisol Enzyme Conjugate Concentrate:
One vial, containing 0.3 mL of a solution of cortisol conjugated to horseradish peroxidase in a protein-based (BSA) buffer with a non-mercury preservative.
